{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01QdFD52hajM9e57XNkPH2nt","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/029-web-output-box-syntax-highlight/plan.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9b3dd130-80ae-4fb4-9b29-3adc75148b02","uuid":"cc78152c-9163-40e5-b8ff-beb2c5cf3fa8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T00:22:33.537Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/029-web-output-box-syntax-highlight/plan.md","oldString":"- [ ] Task 1: Add CSS modifier classes for .output-box.error and .output-box.exit-error in public/styles.css\n- [ ] Task 2: Update exec result handler in public/js/main.js to apply/remove modifier classes based on exitCode and stderr content","newString":"- [x] Task 1: Add CSS modifier classes for .output-box.error and .output-box.exit-error in public/styles.css\n- [x] Task 2: Update exec result handler in public/js/main.js to apply/remove modifier classes based on exitCode and stderr content","originalFile":"# Plan — F-029: Web Output Box Syntax Highlight\n\n## Key Components\n- CSS-only change, no backend or JS modifications\n- Modifier classes on .output-box for semantic states (stderr = error tone, exit code non-zero = warning/danger)\n- JS applies modifier classes dynamically based on exec result values\n\n## Files to Modify\n- `public/styles.css` — add .output-box.error and .output-box.exit-error modifier classes\n- `public/js/main.js` — apply modifier classes after exec result is set\n\n## Data Flow\n1. User runs exec command → API returns exitCode, stdout, stderr\n2. JS sets textContent on each .output-box element\n3. JS also applies CSS modifier class: stderrOutput gets .error if stderr non-empty, exitCodeOutput gets .exit-error if exitCode !== 0\n4. CSS modifier classes style the box with appropriate color palette\n\n## Design Decisions\n- `.output-box.error` — uses existing error palette (#fef3f2 bg, #f9d3d0 border, var(--danger) color) consistent with .message.error and .status.error\n- `.output-box.exit-error` — uses warning palette (--warning color, warning-toned bg) for non-zero exit codes\n- Classes reset on each exec run (remove before re-applying)\n\n## Tasks\n\n- [ ] Task 1: Add CSS modifier classes for .output-box.error and .output-box.exit-error in public/styles.css\n- [ ] Task 2: Update exec result handler in public/js/main.js to apply/remove modifier classes based on exitCode and stderr content\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":22,"oldLines":5,"newStart":22,"newLines":5,"lines":[" "," ## Tasks"," ","-- [ ] Task 1: Add CSS modifier classes for .output-box.error and .output-box.exit-error in public/styles.css","-- [ ] Task 2: Update exec result handler in public/js/main.js to apply/remove modifier classes based on exitCode and stderr content","+- [x] Task 1: Add CSS modifier classes for .output-box.error and .output-box.exit-error in public/styles.css","+- [x] Task 2: Update exec result handler in public/js/main.js to apply/remove modifier classes based on exitCode and stderr content"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
